    <link rel="alternate" href="https://zurich4u.ch/2016/02/18/world-s-only-tree-museum.html"/>
    <id>https://zurich4u.ch/2016/02/18/world-s-only-tree-museum.html</id>
    <published>2016-02-18T11:31:45Z</published>
    <updated>2016-02-24T21:20:29+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Article Author</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="row"&gt;
  &lt;img class="pull-left img-responsive img-thumbnail article" src="/images/f49232c39259e42fc040bda305cbdc8e.jpeg" /&gt;
  &lt;div class="article"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;div&gt;
        Landscape architect Enzo Enea&amp;rsquo;s passion for trees led him to open a park like museum with 300 specimens of different trees, 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        some over 100 years old. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        Works of renowned contemporary artists are shown among the trees. 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        Take the train to Rapperswil and then Bus 622 to Buechstrasse West (takes about 1 hour). 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt;
        Check the website for the opening hours: 
       &lt;a href="http://www.enea.ch"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.enea.ch"&gt;www.enea.ch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/a&gt; 
      &lt;/div&gt; 
      &lt;div&gt; 
       &lt;br&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
    
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="article"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;span/&gt; 
